A modern, scalable microservices-based food delivery platform built with Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, and PostgreSQL.
üöÄ Overview
This platform provides a complete food ordering ecosystem with:
User authentication and management
Restaurant and menu management
Order processing and cart functionality
Real-time notifications via RabbitMQ
API Gateway for centralized routing
Service discovery with Eureka Server
üèóÔ∏è Architecture
The platform follows a microservices architecture with the following services:
Core Services
Front-end (Port 3000)
API Gateway (Port 8080) - Centralized routing and JWT authentication
Eureka Server (Port 8761) - Service discovery and registration
User Service (Port 8083) - User authentication and management
Restaurant Service (Port 8082) - Restaurant and dish management
Order Service (Port 8081) - Order processing and cart functionality
Infrastructure
PostgreSQL - Primary database for each service
Redis - Caching and cart storage
RabbitMQ - Message broker for asynchronous communication
üõ†Ô∏è Technology Stack
Backend
Java 21 - Programming language
Spring Boot 3.x - Framework
Spring Cloud Gateway - API Gateway
Spring Security - Security framework
Spring Data JPA - ORM framework
JWT - Authentication tokens
Flyway - Database migrations
Databases & Caching
PostgreSQL - Primary database
Redis - In-memory data store
RabbitMQ - Message broker
Documentation & Monitoring
Swagger/OpenAPI 3.0 - API documentation
Spring Boot Actuator - Health checks and metrics
üìã Prerequisites
Java 21 or higher
Maven 3.8+
PostgreSQL 14+
Redis 6+
RabbitMQ 3.9+
Docker (optional)
Access the Application
API Gateway: http://localhost:8080
Eureka Dashboard: http://localhost:8761
Swagger UI: http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html
üìñ API Documentation
User Service (Port 8083)
POST /api/auth/register - User registration
POST /api/auth/login - User login
GET /api/users/profile - Get user profile
GET /api/users/{id} - Get user by ID (Admin only)
Restaurant Service (Port 8082)
GET /api/restaurants - Get all restaurants
GET /api/restaurants/{id} - Get restaurant by ID
GET /api/restaurants/{id}/dishes - Get restaurant dishes
POST /api/restaurants - Create restaurant (Admin only)
GET /api/dishes - Get all dishes
POST /api/dishes - Create dish (Admin/Manager)
Order Service (Port 8081)
GET /api/cart - Get user cart
POST /api/cart/items - Add item to cart
POST /api/orders - Create order
GET /api/orders/user/{userId} - Get user orders
GET /api/orders/admin/all - Get all orders (Admin/Manager)
üîê Authentication
The platform uses JWT tokens for authentication:
Register or login to get access token
Include token in Authorization header: Bearer <token>
Tokens expire after 24 hours (access token) and 30 days (refresh token)